<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Comprehensive Pathology: Immunity & Neoplasia Quiz</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary-color: #2c3e50;
            --secondary-color: #16a085;
            --bg-color: #f8f9fa;
            --text-color: #333;
            --card-bg: #ffffff;
            --correct-color: #27ae60;
            --incorrect-color: #c0392b;
            --hint-color: #2980b9;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            color: var(--text-color);
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .quiz-container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: var(--card-bg);
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
        }

        h1 {
            color: var(--primary-color);
            text-align: center;
            border-bottom: 3px solid var(--secondary-color);
            padding-bottom: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        .section-title {
            background-color: var(--primary-color);
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            margin-top: 40px;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
        }

        .question-card {
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
            border-radius: 8px;
            background-color: #fff;
        }

        .question-text {
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: var(--primary-color);
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .options-list {
            list-style-type: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .option-item {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            padding: 12px 15px;
            border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;
            border-radius: 6px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: all 0.2s ease;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .option-item:hover {
            background-color: #f1f5f9;
            border-color: #94a3b8;
        }

        .option-item input[type="radio"] {
            margin-right: 12px;
            transform: scale(1.2);
        }

        .hint-btn {
            background: none;
            border: none;
            color: var(--hint-color);
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            padding: 0;
            margin-top: 10px;
            display: block;
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        .hint-text {
            display: none;
            font-style: italic;
            color: #555;
            background-color: #e3f2fd;
            padding: 10px;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--hint-color);
            border-radius: 4px;
            margin-top: 5px;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        .explanation {
            display: none;
            margin-top: 15px;
            padding: 12px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        .correct-bg {
            background-color: #d4edda !important;
            border-color: var(--correct-color) !important;
            color: #155724;
        }

        .incorrect-bg {
            background-color: #f8d7da !important;
            border-color: var(--incorrect-color) !important;
            color: #721c24;
        }

        .submit-btn {
            display: block;
            width: 100%;
            background-color: var(--secondary-color);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 15px;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            border-radius: 8px;
            cursor: pointer;
            margin-top: 30px;
            transition: background 0.2s ease;
        }

        .submit-btn:hover {
            background-color: #117a65;
        }

        #result-container {
            display: none;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            background-color: #e2e8f0;
            color: var(--primary-color);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="quiz-container">
    <h1>Pathology Assessment: Immunity & Neoplasia</h1>
    
    <form id="quiz-form">
        <!-- SECTION 1 -->
        <div class="section-title">Part 1: Diseases of Immunity (Lecture Notes 1)</div>
        
        <div class="question-card" data-q="1">
            <div class="question-text">1. Which of the following is considered a primary component of innate immunity?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="A"> Skin and mucous membranes</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="B"> Memory T lymphocytes</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="C"> Plasma cells</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="D"> Antigen-specific antibodies</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(1)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-1">Think about the body's non-specific, immediate first line of defense that is always present.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-1"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="2">
            <div class="question-text">2. What is the primary benefit of memory cells in adaptive immunity?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="A"> They provide general protection against any incoming virus.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="B"> They trigger immediate mechanical reflexes like coughing.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="C"> They enable a rapid, highly efficient response upon re-infection.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="D"> They non-specifically phagocytose foreign bacteria.</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(2)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-2">Consider how your body responds much faster the second time it encounters a specific illness.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-2"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="3">
            <div class="question-text">3. Which class of antibody is uniquely capable of crossing the placenta to provide passive immunity to a fetus?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="A"> IgM</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="B"> IgG</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="C"> IgA</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="D"> IgE</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(3)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-3">Look for the most abundant class of circulating immunoglobulins.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-3"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="4">
            <div class="question-text">4. Which cell type represents 60% to 70% of peripheral lymphocytes and expresses a specific rearranged T-cell receptor (TCR)?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="A"> B Lymphocytes</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="B"> Natural Killer (NK) cells</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="C"> T Lymphocytes</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="D"> Macrophages</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(4)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-4">Identify the primary cells responsible for cell-mediated immunity that mature in the thymus.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-4"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="5">
            <div class="question-text">5. Which antibody class is the very first to be produced by B cells during a primary immune response?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="A"> IgM</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="B"> IgG</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="C"> IgD</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="D"> IgE</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(5)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-5">This heavy pentameric immunoglobulin is the default first responder.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-5"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="6">
            <div class="question-text">6. What is the defining characteristic of a hapten (incomplete antigen)?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q6" value="A"> It can activate T cells independently without any processing.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q6" value="B"> It possesses reactivity but lacks immunogenicity on its own.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q6" value="C"> It is always composed of a large, complex protein structure.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q6" value="D"> It stimulates robust antibody production immediately upon entry.</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(6)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-6">Think about a small molecule that can bind to antibodies but requires a carrier protein to trigger an active response.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-6"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="7">
            <div class="question-text">7. Which antibody class is predominantly found in external secretions such as tears, saliva, and mucus?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q7" value="A"> IgA</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q7" value="B"> IgG</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q7" value="C"> IgD</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q7" value="D"> IgM</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(7)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-7">This antibody provides localized mucosal immunity.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-7"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="8">
            <div class="question-text">8. Which of the following organs are classified as primary lymphoid organs?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q8" value="A"> Spleen and lymph nodes</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q8" value="B"> Bone marrow and thymus</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q8" value="C"> Tonsils and Peyer's patches</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q8" value="D"> Appendix and liver</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(8)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-8">Focus on where immune cells are originally generated and matured before entering combat.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-8"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="9">
            <div class="question-text">9. Which antibody class binds selectively to mast cells and basophils, triggering allergic responses?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q9" value="A"> IgG</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q9" value="B"> IgA</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q9" value="C"> IgE</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q9" value="D"> IgM</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(9)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-9">This immunoglobulin is found in trace amounts and is elevated in patients with allergies or asthma.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-9"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="10">
            <div class="question-text">10. What term is used to describe an increased or inappropriate immune response that causes tissue damage?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q10" value="A"> Immunodeficiency</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q10" value="B"> Self-tolerance</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q10" value="C"> Hypersensitivity</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q10" value="D"> Opsonization</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(10)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-10">This word combines a prefix meaning 'excessive' with a root related to environmental awareness.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-10"></div>
        </div>

        <!-- SECTION 2 -->
        <div class="section-title">Part 2: Carcinogenesis (carcinogenesis - MI.pdf)</div>
        
        <div class="question-card" data-q="11">
            <div class="question-text">11. What term defines the multi-step process by which normal cells undergo genetic transformation into cancer cells?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q11" value="A"> Metaplasia</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q11" value="B"> Carcinogenesis</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q11" value="C"> Apoptosis</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q11" value="D"> Homeostasis</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(11)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-11">This word literally translates to the 'origin or creation of cancer'.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-11"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="12">
            <div class="question-text">12. The tendency over time for malignant tumors to become increasingly aggressive and less responsive to therapy is called:</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q12" value="A"> Tumor progression</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q12" value="B"> Clonal stabilizing</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q12" value="C"> Contact inhibition</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q12" value="D"> Innate resolution</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(12)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-12">Think of a word that indicates steady advancement or forward movement.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-12"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="13">
            <div class="question-text">13. Which of the following is an example of a normal cellular gene that promotes growth but can become an oncogene when mutated?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q13" value="A"> Rb gene</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q13" value="B"> APC gene</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q13" value="C"> RAS</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q13" value="D"> WT1 gene</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(13)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-13">This highly common mutated oncogene family acts as a molecular switch in growth factor signaling loops.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-13"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="14">
            <div class="question-text">14. What is the primary action of a functional tumor suppressor gene within a cell?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q14" value="A"> To speed up autonomous growth pathways.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q14" value="B"> To regulate cell division checkpoints and prevent tumor development.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q14" value="C"> To induce continuous DNA damage.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q14" value="D"> To synthesize structural viral proteins.</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(14)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-14">Think of these genes as the protective 'brakes' of the cell cycle.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-14"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="15">
            <div class="question-text">15. How does a mutation leading to overexpression of the BCL2 gene cause tumor formation?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q15" value="A"> By completely neutralizing chemical carcinogens.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q15" value="B"> By preventing apoptosis, allowing damaged cells to survive.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q15" value="C"> By directly accelerating physical tissue abrasion.</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q15" value="D"> By accelerating the repair of pyrimidine dimers.</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(15)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-15">Consider the role of BCL2 as a protective shield against programmed cell suicide.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-15"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="16">
            <div class="question-text">16. Xeroderma Pigmentosum is an inherited skin cancer predisposition caused by a failure in which system?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q16" value="A"> Nucleotide excision repair</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q16" value="B"> Humoral antibody response</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q16" value="C"> Mesenchymal differentiation</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q16" value="D"> Apoptotic caspase cascades</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(16)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-16">This repair system is responsible for removing bulky distortions in DNA, such as those caused by UV light.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-16"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="17">
            <div class="question-text">17. Which of the following viruses is strongly linked to nasopharyngeal carcinoma and Burkitt's lymphoma?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q17" value="A"> Hepatitis B Virus (HBV)</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q17" value="B"> Human Papillomavirus (HPV)</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q17" value="C"> Epstein-Barr Virus (EBV)</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q17" value="D"> Herpes type 8 (HHV-8)</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(17)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-17">This widespread virus causes infectious mononucleosis ('mono') and can lead to specific B-cell and epithelial malignancies.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-17"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="18">
            <div class="question-text">18. Which parasitic infection is directly implicated in the development of urinary bladder carcinoma?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q18" value="A"> Clonorchis sinensis</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q18" value="B"> Schistosomiasis</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q18" value="C"> Plasmodium falciparum</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q18" value="D"> Entamoeba histolytica</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(18)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-18">This disease is caused by a blood fluke that releases eggs into the urinary tract, causing chronic inflammation.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-18"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="19">
            <div class="question-text">19. Clonorchis sinensis (the Chinese liver fluke) is a well-known biological parasite that causes cancer in the:</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q19" value="A"> Bile ducts</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q19" value="B"> Bone marrow</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q19" value="C"> Skin epithelium</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q19" value="D"> Uterine cervix</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(19)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-19">Think about the drainage system of the liver where bile flows.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-19"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="20">
            <div class="question-text">20. Chronic mechanical irritation from poorly fitting dental prosthetics can lead to which condition?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q20" value="A"> Oral squamous cell carcinoma</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q20" value="B"> Burkitt's lymphoma</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q20" value="C"> Hepatocellular carcinoma</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q20" value="D"> Follicular lymphoma</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(20)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-20">Consider the type of cell that lines the inside of the mouth and faces constant physical friction.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-20"></div>
        </div>

        <!-- SECTION 3 -->
        <div class="section-title">Part 3: Diseases of Immunity DMI (Diseases_of_Immunity_DMI.pdf)</div>
        
        <div class="question-card" data-q="21">
            <div class="question-text">21. Which of the following classic clinical features is highly characteristic of Systemic Lupus Erythematosus (SLE)?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q21" value="A"> Claw-like hands</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q21" value="B"> Malar 'butterfly' rash</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q21" value="C"> Swan-neck finger deformities</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q21" value="D"> Barium swallow immotility</label></li>
            </ul>
            <button type="button" class="hint-btn" onclick="toggleHint(21)">Show Hint</button>
            <div class="hint-text" id="hint-21">This rash is named after a winged insect and appears symmetrically across the face.</div>
            <div class="explanation" id="exp-21"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card" data-q="22">
            <div class="question-text">22. Which imaging modality is preferred for evaluating Interstitial Lung Disease (ILD) in a patient with Scleroderma?</div>
            <ul class="options-list">
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q22" value="A"> Barium swallow</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q22" value="B"> High-Resolution Computed Tomography (HRCT)</label></li>
                <li class="option-item"><label><input type="radio" name="q22" value="C"> Abdominal Ultrasound</label></li>
